## 2.  `pcapng.ml` – thin wrapper that declares the external primitives

```ocaml
(* The implementation is deliberately tiny – all the work is done in C++. *)

type t = private Obj.t
type frame = {
  timestamp    : int64;
  captured_len : int;
  original_len : int;
  data         : bytes;
}

external open_file   : string -> t = "pcapng_open_file"
external close       : t -> unit = "pcapng_close"
external iter        : t -> (frame -> unit) -> unit = "pcapng_iter"
external iter_until  : t -> (frame -> bool) -> bool = "pcapng_iter_until"
```

